    <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Darby Felton (darby) on 2007-06-06T13:01:53.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>I was thinking it might make sense to augment the existing Alpha and Alnum filters to provide an option to permit whitespace, off by default, for backward compatibility. Then, the corresponding validation classes would simply proxy the option along to the corresponding filters they use. Thoughts?</p>

        </div>
    </div>
        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Bill Karwin (bkarwin) on 2007-06-10T14:48:31.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>How about do it in a way that encourages subclassing.</p>

<p>For example, make Zend_Validate_Alpha have a boolean property {{$_permitWhitespace}}.  This is set to {{false}} in Zend_Validate_Alpha and {{true} in Zend_Validate_AlphaWS, which extends Zend_Validate_Alpha.</p>

<p>Then Zend_Filter_Alpha takes the optional parameter, as suggested in ZF-1534.</p>

